  <num>42-3209</num>
  <heading>Recovery of real and personal property leased together.</heading>
  <text>Whenever real and personal property are leased together, as, for example, a house with furniture contained therein, the landlord, either in an action of ejectment or in the summary proceeding for possession, in the Superior Court of the District of Columbia, may have a judgment for recovery of the personalty as well as the realty.</text>
